**Guard rail reminder: **All entries are subject to GR-01 through GR-11. Group 10 entries additionally require a developmentalNote field explaining the contamination source. textualLayer is required on every entry and governs which GR-11 tier applies.

**Group 1 — God ****&**** covenant**

**Domain: **god-covenant

The vocabulary of who YHWH is and how he relates to creation and covenant community. These categories define the theological grammar within which all other categories operate.

| **Hebrew / Greek** | **Transliteration** | **Phase** | **Textual layer** | **Correct framing** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| אֱלֹהִים | Elohim | P1 | pre-exilic | God as relational creator and sovereign |
| יהוה | YHWH | P1 | pre-exilic | Personal covenant name — relational presence |
| אֵל שַׁדַּי | El Shaddai | P1 | pre-exilic | God of mountain-power and sovereign provision |
| חֶסֶד | chesed | P1 | pre-exilic | Covenantal loyalty expressed in concrete action |
| אֱמֶת | emeth | P1 | pre-exilic | Covenant faithfulness and reliability |
| בְּרִית | berith | P1 | pre-exilic | Binding covenant relationship |
| אֶמוּנָה | emunah | P2 | pre-exilic | Steadfast faithfulness — the texture of covenant |
| קִנְאָה | qin'ah | P2 | pre-exilic | Zealous covenant passion — not jealousy |
| אֵל עֶלְיוֹן | El Elyon | P2 | pre-exilic | God Most High — sovereign over all nations |
| צְבָאוֹת | tsevaoth | P2 | pre-exilic | LORD of hosts — covenant warrior and sovereign |
| פָּנִים | panim | P2 | pre-exilic | Face/presence — relational directness of God |
| עֵד | ed | P2 | pre-exilic | Witness — covenant testimony and accountability |
| מֶלֶךְ (divine) | melek (divine) | P2 | pre-exilic | YHWH as king — relational sovereign, not tyrant |
| אֵל עוֹלָם | El Olam | P2 | pre-exilic | God of enduring ages |

**Group 2 — Human nature**

**Domain: **human-nature

The vocabulary of what a human being is. The central guard rail: no soul/body dualism. The human person is always a unified, embodied, relational creature.

