| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| נֶפֶשׁ | nephesh | P1 | pre-exilic | Whole animated person — not soul |
| לֵב / לֵבָב | lev/levav | P1 | pre-exilic | Centre of will, thought, and desire |
| בָּשָׂר | basar | P1 | pre-exilic | Creaturely flesh — mortal limitation, not sin |
| רוּחַ | ruach | P1 | pre-exilic | Breath/wind/spirit — animating force |
| יֵצֶר | yetzer | P1 | pre-exilic | Formed inclination — not original sin |
| נְשָׁמָה | neshamah | P2 | pre-exilic | Breath of life breathed by God |
| כְּלָיוֹת | kelayoth | P2 | pre-exilic | Kidneys — seat of deepest emotion |
| מֵעִים | me'im | P2 | pre-exilic | Inward parts — visceral compassion |
| עֶצֶם | etsem | P2 | pre-exilic | Bone — identity, substance, kinship |
| דָּם | dam | P2 | pre-exilic | Blood — life-force, seat of nephesh |
| צֶלֶם | tselem | P2 | pre-exilic | Image/likeness — relational vocation, not ontology |
| אָדָם | adam | P2 | pre-exilic | Humanity as earth-creature — communal, not individual |
| בֶּטֶן | beten | P2 | pre-exilic | Womb/belly — vulnerability and creaturely origin |

