| עָוֹן | avon | P1 | pre-exilic | Twisted distortion — perversion of order |
| פֶּשַׁע | pesha | P1 | pre-exilic | Deliberate covenant rebellion |
| כָּפַר | kaphar | P1 | pre-exilic | Cover/restore — covenantal cleansing, not penal satisfaction |
| פָּדָה | padah | P1 | pre-exilic | Ransom — commercial-framework redemption |
| גָּאַל | ga'al | P1 | pre-exilic | Kinsman redemption — family covenant obligation |
| שׁוּב | shub | P1 | pre-exilic | Turn/return — physical and relational re-orientation |
| אַשְׁמָה | ashmah | P2 | pre-exilic | Guilt as relational damage — not legal verdict |
| רָשָׁע | rasha | P2 | pre-exilic | Wicked — actively disordering the community |
| צַדִּיק | tsaddiq | P2 | pre-exilic | Righteous — living in right-covenant-relationship |
| טָמֵא | tame | P2 | pre-exilic | Unclean — disruption to sacred order, not moral evil |
| טָהוֹר | tahor | P2 | pre-exilic | Clean — restored to covenant wholeness |
| סְלִיחָה | selichah | P2 | pre-exilic | Forgiveness — covenant restoration, not pardon |
| נָקָם | naqam | P2 | pre-exilic | Vengeance — covenant vindication, not revenge |
| כָּפָרָה | kaparah | P2 | pre-exilic | Atonement — the covering act itself |

**Group 6 — Land ****&**** creation**

**Domain: **land-creation

The vocabulary of the physical world as covenantal space. Creation in the Hebrew frame is not a scientific account — it is a theological claim about ordered, relational space.

