| שֹׁפֵט | shophet | P2 | pre-exilic | Judge — covenant order-restorer, not punisher |
| מֶלֶךְ (human) | melek (human) | P2 | pre-exilic | King under covenant obligation to community |
| עָנִי | ani | P2 | pre-exilic | Poor — covenant community's obligation recipient |
| יָתוֹם | yatom | P2 | pre-exilic | Orphan — covenant community's charge |
| אַלְמָנָה | almanah | P2 | pre-exilic | Widow — covenant community's charge |
| גֵּר | ger | P2 | pre-exilic | Sojourner — covenant hospitality obligation |
| זָקֵן | zaqen | P2 | pre-exilic | Elder — covenant wisdom bearer |
| חָזוֹן | chazon | P2 | pre-exilic | Vision — prophetic covenant sight |
| אוֹת | ot | P2 | pre-exilic | Sign — covenant marker and witness event |
| שׁוֹמֵר | shomer | P2 | pre-exilic | Watchman — covenant faithfulness keeper |

**Group 8 — Eschatology ****&**** hope**

**Domain: **eschatology-hope

The vocabulary of what God brings to completion. Hebrew eschatology is always communal and historical — not the evacuation of creation but its restoration.

