| תִּקְוָה | tiqvah | P2 | pre-exilic | Hope — a cord stretched toward promised future |
| עוֹלָם | olam | P2 | pre-exilic | Age/eternity — enduring covenant time, not timelessness |
| גְּאֻלָּה | geulah | P2 | pre-exilic | Corporate redemption — community restoration |
| גָּלוּת | galut | P2 | exilic | Exile — covenant rupture, not just geography |
| שׁוּב שְׁבוּת | shuv shevut | P2 | exilic | Return from exile — full covenant restoration |
| חַיִּים | chayyim | P2 | pre-exilic | Life — covenant vitality, not mere biological existence |
| מָוֶת | mavet | P2 | pre-exilic | Death — covenant separation, not annihilation |
| שְׁאוֹל | sheol | P2 | pre-exilic | Place of the dead — not hell, not purgatory, not reward/punishment |
| תְּחִיַּת הַמֵּתִים | techiyat hametim | P2 | post-exilic | Resurrection — bodily covenant restoration |
| נֶחָמָה | nechamah | P2 | pre-exilic | Comfort — covenant restoration-promise enacted |
| אַחֲרִית | acharit | P2 | pre-exilic | End/future — what God brings to covenant completion |

**Group 9 — NT / LXX distinctive**

**Domain: **nt-lxx-distinctive

NT Greek vocabulary routed through its LXX antecedents. Every NT word in this group carries a Hebrew category. Greek is the vehicle. Hebrew is the thought.

